The paper deals with the problem of learning decentralized control policies for multi-robot swarm environments, which is a typical problem in the field of multi-agent systems (MAS). Therefore, cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes the use of deep reinforcement learning (RL) to learn these policies, which falls under the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also deals with the problem of controlling the behavior of robots, which is a typical problem in the field of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also proposes the use of Trust Region Policy Optimization (TRPO), which is a popular RL algorithm, falling under the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper deals with the problem of coordinating the behavior of multiple agents, which is a typical problem in the field of control systems (cs.SY).
